com.team08storyapp

Class Video

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.team08storyapp.Video
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Video
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ ++++++ This class is used for future implementations (Fake Class)++++++ +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ Video is a model class representing an soundtrack or recording that can be used in an Annotation on a StoryFragment in a Story or as an illustration on a StoryFragment in a Story. An photo has the following properties:
    • Video Id is to uniquely identify the Video.
    • Video Name is the name the user gave to the Video track.
    • Video the Video the reader set in Annotation.
    • Encoded Video is the video encoded for storing it in a file or on a webservice.
    • Video Permissions is the track's permission for read only
    These properties are able to be accessed through the constructor or through public getters/setters.
    Since:
    1.0

    1.0 November 8, 2013
